A strong earthquake struck the southern Philippines  before dawn Saturday, toppling power and communication lines in Pagadian City,  but there were no immediate reports of casualties, seismologists here said.
The temblor, striking at 4:12 a.m. (2012 GMT Friday), registered 5.7 on  the Richter scale and its epicenter was plotted in Illana Bay, a few  kilometers (miles) south of Pagadian, seismologist Lito Lanuza of the  Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology told AFP.
